Frons above clypeus forming sharp ridge, the latter not carinate; mesal portion of disc weakly convex in lateral view, evenly; U-shaped frontal impression shallow. Temples abruptly narrowed just behind eyes, almost smooth. Occipital ridge indistinct. Antenna (
Fig. 25
) with scape rather conical, not compressed; short and dense pubescence present only on antennomeres 5–11; antennomere 11 evenly expanded on basal two-thirds and apically rounded, slightly compressed. Pronotum (
Fig. 27
) with hypomera lacking transverse ridge. Scutellum with anterior margin rounded. Elytral disc without notable relief.
